message.content: cs.HCI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SI. The paper focuses on the use of an autocompletion user interface (AUI) in crowdsourcing tasks, which is relevant to the subfield of human-computer interaction (HCI). The study also involves analyzing the textual responses of workers, which falls under the subfield of computational linguistics (CL). Additionally, the use of word2vec to measure semantic diversity suggests a connection to natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Finally, the study's focus on improving efficiency and information gathering in crowdsourcing could be relevant to the subfield of social computing (SI).
